<figureCitation id="A3922A050D0EB60CFAC9FBE4FAD8F85C" box="[1290,1374,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1389,1411]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,468,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-145@11.[151,1436,461,1364]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Geographic distribution in the Mexican territory of:A. L. cruciata, L. lasiocarpum, L. lewisii, L. mexicanum, and L. tenellum; B. L. elongatum, L. neomexicanum, L. puberulum, L. rzedowskii, and L. schiedeanum; C. L. modestum, L. orizabae, L. pringlei, L. scabrellum, and L. vernale. Maps by Ma. Isabel Olivares." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6622771/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="161">Fig. 5b</figureCitation>
